{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":172706,"duration_api_ms":172588,"num_turns":6,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"b34e9402-4165-44f7-a4f4-8eb175e51024","total_cost_usd":0.55754505,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":34355,"cache_read_input_tokens":207319,"output_tokens":4282,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":34355,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":4282,"cacheReadInputTokens":207319,"cacheCreationInputTokens":34355,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.42546324999999996,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":81,"outputTokens":8938,"cacheReadInputTokens":418333,"cacheCreationInputTokens":36382,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.13208180000000003,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Accept the two concrete correctness fixes (fr-13-36f0aa72 and fr-13-a74a46a6) as they address real bugs in recency comparison and idempotency recovery. Reject fr-13-ca8af530 because the cross-naming collapse is intentional legacy backfill behavior guarded by legacy_group_accepts_completion's run_id.is_none() check. Reject fr-13-8f43b7ad because the proposed remedy (test/documentation) does not actually fix the clock-skew ordering issue it identifies.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-13-ca8af530","decision":"reject","rationale":"The fallback from a named terminal entry to unique_open_legacy_group_index is intentional backfill behavior. legacy_group_accepts_completion (model.rs:526-535) already gates on existing.run_id.is_none() AND existing.started_at == entry.started_at, so the collapse only occurs when a named completion shares the exact bead_id, project_id, and started_at of a legacy unnamed Running entry — precisely the case where the completion is retroactively naming the same attempt. Adding an entry.run_id.is_none() guard before the fallback would break this backfill path and leave legacy starts that are later completed with a run_id as permanently open orphans. The existing test explicit_retry_after_legacy_open_appends_new_attempt already validates that entries with different started_at remain distinct."},{"amendment_id":"fr-13-8f43b7ad","decision":"reject","rationale":"The clock-skew scenario is a real limitation of using started_at as the recency signal, but the proposed amendment only asks for a test or documentation of the monotonicity assumption. A test would either codify buggy behavior (showing the wrong entry wins) or merely assert existing correct behavior under normal conditions — neither is a fix. Documentation of the assumption doesn't enforce it. A real remedy would require an additional causal ordering signal (e.g., a monotonic sequence counter), which is a different scope of change than what this amendment proposes. Without a concrete correctness fix, accepting this would just add test/doc overhead without improving robustness."},{"amendment_id":"fr-13-36f0aa72","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is a real correctness bug. In compare_task_run_recency (model.rs:379-390), when two entries share the same started_at, finished_at is compared next. A terminal entry with finished_at=T+N beats a running retry whose finished_at defaults to started_at=T, so the terminal entry wins the recency contest. latest_task_runs_per_bead then selects the stale terminal entry, causing reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage to find no active bead and set in_progress_beads=0 and status=Ready despite an active retry. The fix needs a deterministic tie-break that ranks a Running entry above a terminal entry when started_at is equal, since the running state represents a newer attempt. A regression test with same-timestamp retries affecting snapshot state should accompany the fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-13-a74a46a6","decision":"accept","rationale":"The idempotency gap is real and verifiable in the code. find_matching_running_task_run (model.rs:439-443) for run_id=None only matches when the single running entry has the exact same started_at as the retry. If record_bead_start succeeds at writing lineage and snapshot but fails at journal append, a runless retry with a new timestamp (common when callers use Utc::now()) will not match the existing running row, fall through past the matching_running_entries check, hit the active_beads.contains(bead_id) guard, and return an unrecoverable 'already active' error. Named callers avoid this because run_id matching is timestamp-independent. Widening the runless match to accept a unique running entry for the same bead/project regardless of started_at (when there's exactly one candidate) is a sound idempotency fix that mirrors the named-caller recovery path."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"2200b81d-c7fe-435c-a971-7f5054f2dbcd"}
